A film by Praveen K
Produced by Vishnu Vishal Studioz

DOP - Harish Kannan
Music - Ghibran 
Editor - San Lokesh
Stunts - Stunt Silva, PC Stunts Prabhu
Additional Screenplay - Manu Anand
Production Design - S. Jayachandran
Costume Designer and Stylist - Vinod Sundar 
Additional styling - Varshini Sankar
Sound Design - Sachin Sudhakaran, Hariharan N (Sync Cinema) 
Audiography -  Tapas Nayak
DI -  Bridge PostWorks

Dubbing - Seed Studios 
Publicity Designs - Prathool NT
PRO - Sathish (AIM), Vamsi Shekar 
Post Production Supervisor - Gunashekar (Post Office)
Marketing and Promotions - Siddarth Srinivas
Executive Producers - Seetharam
Creative Producer - Shravanthi Sainath

snippet.title: Kantara Chapter 1 Pre-Release Event Announcement Trailer | Rishab Shetty | NTR | ShreyasMedia
snippet.description:
Watch Kantara Chapter 1 Pre-Release Event Announcement Trailer on #ShreyasMedia 


#KantaraChapter1PreReleaseEvent #AnnouncementTrailer
#KantaraChapter1 #RishabShetty #Kantara #ALegend #DivineEpic #VijayKiragandu #AjaneeshLoknath #RukminiVasanth #GulshanDevaiah #Jayaram #KantaraTrailer #KantaraChapter1Trailer #Kantarachapter1onOct2 #KantaraTeluguTrailer #KantaraChapter1TeluguTrailer 

The makers behind KGF: Chapter 1 & 2 and Salaar ‚Äî and the visionary, National Award‚Äìwinning Filmmaker and Actor Rishab Shetty, comes the official trailer for Kantara: A Legend ‚Äì Chapter 1. 

Starring Rishab Shetty as Berme, Rukmini Vasanth as Kanakavathi, and Gulshan Devaiah as Kulashekara, supported by a formidable ensemble cast.With a soul-stirring score by B. Ajaneesh Loknath and produced by Vijay Kiragandur under Hombale Films, Kantara: A Legend ‚Äì Chapter 1 promises visceral action, haunting melodies, and a saga that will echo through generations. 

Witness India's Divine Epic on Screens this 2 October 2025. 

Movie Credits-

Produced by: Vijay Kiragandur

Stunt Choreographers: Arjun Raj, Todor Lazarov (Juji), Ram-Laxman, Mahesh Mathew, Mithun Singh Rajput
Dance Choreographers: Bhushan, Swaraj Shetty
Line Producers: Suhas Shetty, Akshay Bellad
Direction Department: Srikanth Puppala(Signature), Shivaachiranthanaa, Nithesh Nanjundaradhya, Rakesh Bj, Dhanush K G, Vikas Mohare, Dollar, Balakrishna Yadav, Sajan Pai, Arunlal C S, R Krishna prasad, Shreepathi Kadasooru, Sharath Kumar J

Trailer mashups are often created for a movie that does not exist now or to change the genre of an existing film. These are derivative works and as such, may find protection from copyright claims under the doctrine of fair use. The trailer mashups are not only a user-generated form of digital creativity but a way to create anticipation for future releases, working in tandem with current movie trailers. Movie trailers are designed to give minimal plot detail and to create hype and anticipation. Fan-made trailer mashups allow the audience to perform their own cinematic spin on current movie footage. This allows the trailer to focus on a specific actor or portion of the film. It could even change the plot or genre of the film entirely.

snippet.title: Why Are Bollywood Trailers Spoiling Everything?
snippet.description:
There is a genuine problem happening in #bollywood where movie trailers are revealing key plot points. This is true for both the trailers of the upcoming movie #thamma and #sunnysanskarikitulsikumari . What is the urgency to not only release twists but cameos also in the trailer. I have covered several other movies that have fallen prey to the same. I hope you like the video on:-

snippet.title: Tumse Behtar | Varun D, Janhvi K, Sanya M, Rohit S | Tanishk B, Arijit S, Manoj M | SSKTK
snippet.description:
You‚Äôve seen them dance, you‚Äôve seen them fall in love, now witness the heartbreak when love gets intertwined! Presenting ‚ÄòTumse Behtar‚Äô from ‚ÄòSunny Sanskari Ki Tulsi Kumari‚Äô, starring Varun Dhawan, Janhvi Kapoor, Sanya Malhotra and Rohit Saraf. Composed by Tanishk Bagchi and written by Manoj Muntashir, this beautiful song is sung by Arijit Singh.

#TumseBehtar #ArijitSingh #TanishkBagchi #SSKTK

Music Composer: Tanishk Bagchi
Lyricist: Manoj Muntashir
Singer: Arijit Singh
Music Producer: Tanishk Bagchi & Krishna Kishor
Woodwinds: Nikhil Ram
Keys: Navneeth, Anoop, Melvin
Male Chorus: Rahul, Sanjay, Abijith, Aston
Female Chorus: Kamalaja, Fathima, Nayansi, Aarthi
Arijit Singh's Vocals Recorded by: Sukanto Singha
Arijit Singh‚Äôs Recordings Managed by: Ashish Biswal
Mixed and Mastered by: Eric Pillai @ Future Sounds of Bombay
Assistant Mix Engineer: Michael Edwin Pillai @ Future Sounds of Bombay
Music Supervisor: Azeem Dayani and Varun Dhawan
Sr Associate Music Supervisor: Tanvi Asher
Jr Associate Music Supervisor: Vasundhara Misra
Music Team: Heer Kamdar

Dharma Productions & Mentor Disciple Entertainment present 
A Dharma Productions Film
Starring Varun Dhawan, Janhvi Kapoor, Sanya Malhotra, & Rohit Saraf
Directed by Shashank Khaitan
Produced by Hiroo Yash Johar, Karan Johar, Adar Poonawalla, Apoorva Mehta & Shashank Khaitan
Co-produced by Marijke deSouza 
Written by Shashank Khaitan
Dialogues by Shashank Khaitan & Ishita Moitra

Lyrics:
Tumhara-mera milna likha to hoga kahin
Naseebon ka sitara, mila to hoga Kahin

Na Jane kyun ae humnasheen
Hai mere dil ko ye yaqeen
Ki tum sang ho to, bigdi baatein, saari ban jayengi
Tum jo has do, roothi raatein saari man jayengi

Tumse behtar, tumse pyara yaara koi nahin
Aasmaa pe, tumse roshan, tara koi nahin!

Raaton me, bina tumhare ghabrayein, ghabraayein
Khwaabon me, milo agar khush ho jaayein ho jaayein

Chain ho tum aaram ho shayad
Koi sukoon ki shaam ho shayad
Khushi kahoon ya dil ki tasalli
Kya tumhein doon main naam

Kitabein dekhi saari, mili na koi shaayri
Tareefein karoon kaise, yahi hai muhskil meri

Na Jane kyun a humnasheen
Hai mere dil ko ye yaqeen
Ki tum sang ho to, bigdi baatein, saari ban jayengi
Tum jo has do, roothi raatein saari man jayengi
Jo daraeyin wo hawayein gham ki, tham jayengi

Tumse behtar, tumse pyara yaara koi nahin
Aasmaa pe, tumse roshan, tara koi nahin!

Dekho na ye kamaal hua hai
Aesa dil ka haal hua hai
Dil mera tere itar me dooba
Jaise koi roomal hua hai

Aesi hai khwahish dil me mere
Jaane mujhe sab naam se tere
Aesi diwangi pahle nahin thee
Haal ye pichhle saal hua hai

Tumse behtar, tumse pyara yaara koi nahin
Aasmaa pe, tumse roshan, tara koi nahin!

Koi nahin tumse behtar, tumse pyaara
Tumse zyaada mera koi nahin!

snippet.title: MANIKYA DEBI MAA MANIKESWARI || Abhilipsa Panda || Chhatar Jatra || Kalahandi Song || Official Video
snippet.description:
Rockstar Abhilipsa Panda presents 
üå∏üôè MANIKYA DEBI MAA MANIKESWARI üôèüå∏
On the divine occasion of Chhatar Jatra 2025, we humbly dedicate this bhakti geet to Maa Manikeswari, the presiding deity of Kalahandi and Bhawanipatna.

‚ú® Why we celebrate Chhatar Jatra?
Chhatar Jatra is one of the most vibrant and spiritual festivals of Western Odisha, celebrated during Durga Puja (Ashwina month). The symbolic ‚ÄúChhatar‚Äù (umbrella) of Maa Manikeswari is carried from the temple to Jenakhala for tantric rituals, and then returned in a grand procession with thousands of devotees, folk music like Ghumura, and offerings of faith.

üå∫ About Maa Manikeswari
Maa Manikeswari is regarded as the protector and royal deity of Kalahandi, worshipped for strength, prosperity, and protection. Her worship beautifully blends tribal traditions and Hindu rituals, making her one of the most unique goddesses of Odisha.

üé∂ Through this song, we seek her blessings for peace, courage, and devotion in every heart.

üôè Jaya Maa Manikeswari! üôè

Don‚Äôt forget to LIKE, SHARE & SUBSCRIBE for more devotional songs.
üîî Stay tuned for divine bhajans & Odia cultural music.

Maa Manikeswari is regarded as the protector and royal deity of Kalahandi, worshipped for strength, prosperity, and protection. Her worship beautifully blends tribal traditions and Hindu rituals, making her one of the most unique goddesses of Odisha.
